## Additional Notes on the Test Setup (for the diagram)
- This was a pure simulation for the "client runs tlsn verifier crate, expert runs tlsn prover crate" as requested.
- min_mix_hops=3 was modeled by injecting 375 ms one-way sleeps (chosen to represent ~750 ms RTT for a 3-hop path; real hop latency would vary by region/queuing).
- The duplex socket between prover and verifier in the example stood in for "the channel tunneled over the mixnet".
- Real integration would require a small RPC or stream abstraction to carry the tlsn Session bytes inside sphinx packets (or using the REACH low-latency return path for some messages).
- Geographic locations are plausible assumptions for a global privacy mixnet (different legal jurisdictions for hops to provide the anonymity set). No real nodes were deployed in those cities for this run; the sleeps stood in for the path latency.
- Number of round-trips: 8 one-way phase messages logged. The underlying 2PC has many more tiny wire messages; our instrumentation only tagged the coarse phase boundaries around the sleeps.
- Total setup time (MPC session + config + preprocessing + 2PC TLS handshake + app data + proof): ~2.6 s in the measured test logic for this run (dominated by the 8 × 375 ms = 3 s of simulated network).

